Title: Family Guy: Season 11, Volume 12

reviewText: Can Seth McFarlane can write a bad episode of Family Guy?  Judging from the episodes in this collection the answer appears to be an emphatic NO.There seems (subjectively) to be a greater number of deleted scenes (in some episodes) than in previous collections.It's hard to pick favorites, but if I had to, I'd say that Yug Yilmaf and Space Camp particularly shine.
Title: Family Guy: Season 11, Volume 12

reviewText: Am a huge fan of the show. Vol 11 and all previous volumes play in my DVD player. The player is a Panasonic, only about a year and a half old. These discs won't play. I sent them back. Amazon sent a replacement right away. The new ones won't play. I called the number on the box for Fox Searchlight. They said the haven't heard other complaints like this. Will keep you posted.
summary: I'd love it if only it played in my DVD player

Title: Family Guy: Season 11, Volume 12

reviewText: Well Seth & co. have done it again & put out a full season (Season 11) on DVD. This volume celebrates the 200th episode - "Yug Ylimaf".Not to mention the controversial "Turban Cowboy". Not really a favorite season, but I still love these characters & still get a chuckle while watching them! The uncensored episodes do add to the comedy.
